{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the routine use of visual estimation of stenosis in CAG, this approach lacks standardization and shows high intra-observer and inter-observer variability, generally ranging from 6.9% to 26.4% between observers 9.",
    "Yet, this visual assessment remains the clinical standard for assessing CAD severity 4, 10, 11 and is also endorsed by clinical guidelines 12, 13.",
    "Quantitative coronary angiography (QCA) offers more reproducible results but requires clinician input for image selection and is resource-intensive, thus leading to its predominant use in research 5, [14] [15] [16].",
    "Adjunctive testing, such as physiological assessments (e.g.",
    "fractional flow reserve; FFR) 17 and intra-vascular imaging 18, supplements CAD evaluation during coronary angiography."
  ]
}